9 (iii) “Dwelling house”:
10 1. means real property that is:
11 A. the legal residence of a disabled veteran or a surviving
12 spouse; and
13 B. occupied by not more than two families; and
14 2. includes the lot or curtilage and structures necessary to
15 use the real property as a residence.
16 (iv) “Surviving spouse” means an individual who has not remarried
17 and who is the surviving spouse of a disabled veteran.
18 (2) The governing body of Washington County may grant, by law, a
19 property tax credit under this subsection against the county property tax imposed on a
20 dwelling house if:
21 (i) the dwelling house is owned by:
22 1. a disabled veteran; or
23 2. a surviving spouse of a disabled veteran, if:
24 A. the dwelling house was owned by the disabled veteran at
25 the time of the disabled veteran’s death; and
26 B. the surviving spouse meets the requirements of paragraph
27 (4) of this subsection; and
28 (ii) the application requirements of paragraph (5) of this subsection
29 are met.

