1 (3) The property tax credit granted under this subsection shall equal a
2 percentage of the amount of property tax imposed on the dwelling house that is equal to
3 the percentage of the disabled veteran’s service–connected disability rating.
4 (4) After a disabled veteran dies, the surviving spouse of the disabled
5 veteran may receive a disabled veteran’s property tax credit for the dwelling house that
6 was formerly owned by the disabled veteran if:
7 (i) the dwelling house received a property tax credit under this
8 subsection; and
9 (ii) the surviving spouse owns and resides in the dwelling house.
10 (5) (i) A disabled veteran or a surviving spouse of a disabled veteran
11 shall apply for the property tax credit under this subsection by providing to the county:
12 1. a copy of the disabled veteran’s discharge certificate from
13 active military, naval, or air service; and
14 2. on the form provided by the county, a certification of the
15 disabled veteran’s disability from the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs.
16 (ii) The disabled veteran’s certificate of disability may not be
17 inspected by individuals other than:
18 1. the disabled veteran; or
19 2. appropriate employees of the county.
20 (6) The governing body of Washington County may provide, by law, for:
21 (i) the duration of the tax credit;
22 (ii) regulations and procedures for the application and uniform
23 processing of requests for the tax credit; and
24 (iii) any other provision necessary to carry out the tax credit under
25 this subsection.
26 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
27 1, 2025, and shall be applicable to all taxable years beginning after June 30, 2025.

